column2: Additional development work was conducted under subsequent programs through 2005. Most notably, the Second

column1: Generation Reusable Launch Vehicle Program sponsored the GRCop-84 mechanical property database development
for the RS-83 and RS-84 engines. The goal of the program was to achieve 100 missions before an engine overhaul
and a 500-mission life. While the engines were never built and tested, the mechanical properties indicated that the
goals could be met by a GRCop-84 liner.
